Attention is permutation-invariant — if you shuffle the words "cat sat the mat on", the attention scores are identical. 
It has no built-in sense of order.
Positional encoding fixes this by injecting a position signal directly into each token's 
embedding before it enters the transformer.
The core idea: add a unique vector to each token's embedding that encodes its position in the sequence. 
The model can then learn to use position as a feature, just like semantic meaning.
